data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"---\n\n## Pod Creation — Failed\n\n**Root Cause:** The Kubernetes MCP server has **no valid kubeconfig loaded**. All three diagnostic calls confirm the same error:\n\n```\nKubernetes client initialization failed: Invalid kube-config file. No configuration found.\n```\n\nThe Azure AKS credential fetch also failed with the recurring **Admin MCP internal error** (`Attempt to overwrite 'args' in LogRecord`).\n\n---\n\n## Diagnosis\n\n| Check | Result | Status |\n|-------|--------|:------:|\n| **`k8s_apply_yaml`** | No kubeconfig found | ❌ |\n| **`k8s_get_current_context`** | No kubeconfig found | ❌ |\n| **`k8s_list_contexts`** | No kubeconfig found | ❌ |\n| **`azure_list_aks_clusters`** | Admin MCP internal error | ❌ |\n\nThis is consistent with **previous conversation history** — the Kubernetes MCP has been intermittently losing its kubeconfig, and the Admin MCP has the known `LogRecord` bug.\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Remediation\n\n| Priority | Action | Details |\n|:--------:|--------|---------|\n| **P0** | **Re-inject kubeconfig into the K8s MCP server** | Run `azure_get_aks_credentials` from a working shell, or mount the kubeconfig as a Secret/ConfigMap into the MCP proxy pod |\n| **P0** | **Restart the MCP proxy deployment** | `kubectl rollout restart deployment/openagentic-mcp-proxy -n openagentic` from a host with direct cluster access |\n| **P1** | **Persist kubeconfig via volume mount** | The kubeconfig appears ephemeral — mount it from a Kubernetes Secret so it survives pod restarts |\n\n> **Note:** This is the same infrastructure failure pattern observed in previous audits. The MCP proxy pod either crashed or was rescheduled and lost its in-memory kubeconfig. Until a cluster admin re-provisions credentials from outside this tool chain, all `k8s_*` operations will fail.\n\nWant me to retry after you've restored the kubeconfig, or attempt an alternative path?"}

